                                <h1>Zhi Yang</h1>
                                <p>Associate Professor @ Peking University</p>
                            </header>
                            <p>I received my Ph.D.degree in Computer Science from Peking University in 2010, and my
                                B.S. degree in Computer Science
                                from Harbin Institute of Technology in 2005. My Ph.D.advisor is Prof. Yafei Dai.</p>
                            <p>My research interests include:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><b>Efficient parallel systems for large-scale data analytics</b>, e.g., graph
                                    processing, deep learning acceleration, through
                                    leveraging modern hardware like GPU.</li>
                                <li><b>Design and optimization of distributed systems</b>, e.g., distributed storage,
                                    P2P system, fault tolerance, and performance
                                    modeling and optimization.</li>
                                <li><b>Social network application</b>, e.g., sybil detection, graph and behavioral
                                    models in online social networks.</li>
                            </ul>
